"n":{"docs":{"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/personal-blog/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}}},"o":{"docs":{},"df":0,"s":{"docs":{},"df":0,"t":{"docs":{"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/posts/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}},"r":{"docs":{},"df":0,"o":{"docs":{},"df":0,"j":{"docs":{},"df":0,"e":{"docs":{},"df":0,"c":{"docs":{},"df":0,"t":{"docs":{"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}}}}},"t":{"docs":{},"df":0,"a":{"docs":{},"df":0,"s":{"docs":{},"df":0,"a":{"docs":{},"df":0,"r":{"docs":{"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}}}}}},"documentStore":{"save":true,"docs":{"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/":{"body":"Systems &amp; Performance\nI like software that has to work under real constraints: correctness,\nspeed, and long-term maintainability all at once. Most of my Rust work\nlives here, from small tools to bigger data pipelines.\n3D &amp; Geospatial\nMy passion sits in Geoinformatics Software Engineering, which means a lot of maps, point\nclouds, AI, and 3D reconstruction. I write about what I learn wiring these\npieces together, including my ongoing dive into Structure from Motion.\nFull Stack Development\nI'm care about crafting visually stunning, simple, intuitive UIs and\npairing them with clean, well-built APIs. I enjoy the full loop of\nturning an idea into something people can actually use, from pixel\ndetails up through backend architecture.\nLearning in the Open\nThis site is where I document what I'm building, what broke, and what\nI learned fixing it. Mostly technical, occasionally the life stuff too.","description":"","id":"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/","path":"/","title":"Mahmut Tasar"},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/about/":{"body":"","description":"","id":"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/about/","path":"/about/","title":"About"},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/posts/":{"body":"","description":"","id":"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/posts/","path":"/posts/","title":"Posts"},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/":{"body":"","description":"","id":"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/","path":"/projects/","title":"Projects"},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/personal-blog/":{"body":"For a while, I wanted to have my own website, but I didn't want to build everything from scratch. I was looking for something that was ready to use and easy to get started with.\nThanks to Orhun Parmaksız that introduced me to Zola, a static site generator written in Rust, and it seemed like the perfect fit.\nApollo\nZola offers many themes that you can choose. I decided to go with Apollo because I like its minimalistic and modern design.\nHow to Set It Up\nTo set everything up, I followed this blog post by Orhun Parmaksız along with the Apollo documantation. Everything I needed was already covered there.","description":"A blog created with Zola - Apollo Theme","id":"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/personal-blog/","path":"/projects/personal-blog/","title":"Personal Blog"}},"docInfo":{"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/":{"body":94,"description":0,"path":0,"title":2},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/about/":{"body":0,"description":0,"path":0,"title":0},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/posts/":{"body":0,"description":0,"path":1,"title":1},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/":{"body":0,"description":0,"path":1,"title":1},"https://tasarma.github.io/tasarma.github.io/pr-preview/pr-9/projects/personal-blog/":{"body":55,"description":5,"path":3,"title":2}},"length":5},"lang":"English"}